Step 1 : Create application class by extending Stateless.
         Override build method and return home screen

Step 2 : Create a custom MyAppBar() extending StatefulWidget implements PreferredSizeWidget
         Create a constructor(******String title******)
         Create _MyAppBarState and return in MyAppBar createState Method
         Now we can directly use appBar in any of the pages by calling MyAppBar(*****"Some Title"****)

Step 3 : Create SplashPage (Stateful)
         Create _SplashPageState and return in SplashPage createState Method
         Similarly Create SplashUi(Stateful) and return it from build method of _SplashPageState
         Override initState() to initialize Timer
         Create Navigator with pushReplacement and pass the LoginPage()

Step 4 : Create UserData Class to hole email and phno
         It will hold the data for login page input fields

Step 5 : Create LoginPage (Stateful)
         Create _LoginPageState and return in LoginPage createState Method
         Similarly Create LoginUi(Stateless) and return it from build method of _SplashPageState
         Build the UI in LoginUi build method
         Create a button on Pressing which pass Navigator with *********UserData() object********

Step 6 : Create DashPage (Stateful) with a constructor(**********UserData*********)
         Create _DashPageState and return in DashPage createState Method.
         In build Method of _DashPageState return DashUi(********widget.userData********)
         Similarly Create DashUi(StatefulWidget) with a constructor(UserData)
         In _DashUiState retrieve the ********widget.userData******** and populate UI.


